 The DP and his team are set to make a series of stopovers that will begin with the commissioning of a community water project at Jamaica area in Gìthùngùri Constituency. The Kenya Kwanza convoy will then head to Kambaa, Kamburu and Kahuruko shopping centres where they will address roadside gatherings. In the afternoon the team will make similar stopovers at Kagwe and Mungngere shopping centres. Meanwhile, the Azimio La Umoja movement led by Raila Odinga prepares for a four-day tour of the Coast region. The Azimio team will begin their foray into the Coast region in Kilifi on Saturday then head to Mombasa on Sunday. On Monday, the Odinga's brigade will be in Kwale County before wrapping up the tour in Taita Taveta on Tuesday. At the same time, NARC party led by Kitui Governor Charity Ngilu is holding its National Delegates Conference (NDC) at the Bomas of Kenya. 